"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hhx1665702796499.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hhx1665702796499.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hhx1665702796499.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hhx1665702796499\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Snippet Library Editor\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Snippet Library Editor to create and edit code snippets.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hhx1665702796499__section_w23ab1b7b1_w24ab1b7_w25ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hhx1665702796499__section_w26ab1b7b3_w27ab1b7_w28ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838173e60\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhx1665702796499__li_d2711e1_d2712e1_d2713e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ggq1704451054026.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ggq1704451054026.html\" title=\"You can create and organize snippets of ProcScript, JavaScript, HTML other text in snippet libraries.\">Create a Snippet</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhx1665702796499__li_d2714e1_d2715e1_d2716e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hhx1665702796499__li_d2717e1_d2718e1_d2719e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/biv1704450635249.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Snippets</a><p>Snippets are named fragments of code or text that you can insert into your application script or layout to speed development. They are defined as development objects in snippet libraries.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528217\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528217\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Snippet Library Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Snippet Library Editor Use the Snippet Library Editor to create and edit code snippets. How to Create a Snippet Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Snippets Snippets are named fragments of code or text that you can insert into your application script or layout to speed development. They are defined as development objects in snippet libraries. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}